},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test structure**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a self-contained inner record in the same test file and possibly adding metadata entries for an existing enum. I need to ensure this stays within the test file itself. However, there are already unstaged changes in reachability-metadata.json. If I edit it, those unrelated modifications will be included in the commit unless I’m careful. I could either leave it untouched or selectively stage my changes using git add -p or by specifying the commit path directly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing runtime reflection**\\n\\nI’m considering the runtime reflection call on the class object and wondering why the existing record test isn’t showing any coverage. Maybe TrackDynamicAccess only reports calls on application classes, which could be the reason. It’s interesting to think about what might be causing this gap. I want to track it down to get a clearer understanding of how coverage is being reported!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_4sE6pvsDsSpTxas0aD8r7htB|fc_0ea263f7477fc9fd0169f02f136bf0819497272f4283d436d1", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find stats -path '*com.fasterxml.jackson.jr*jackson-jr-objects*2.21.0*' -type f | sort", "timeout": 20}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_d7YhUPwwgZ5EjzHgxGnGqazw|fc_0ea263f7477fc9fd0169f02f136bf88194916ab70368f45b69", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find . -path '*dynamic-access*' -o -path '*ValueReaderLocator*report*' | sort", "timeout": 20}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yBfH1IBnqSfg6YdSJUWMe9JO|fc_0ea263f7477fc9fd0169f02f136c008194ac4c2b6fdde83695", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtils.java", "offset": 1, "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.4", "usage": {"input": 3280, "output": 1275, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40907, 